HEADWORD: Chaconne
<hw>Cha*conne"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Sp.
<ets>chacona</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An old Spanish dance
in moderate three-four measure, like the Passacaglia, which is slower.
Both are used by classical composers as themes for variations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

